{"questionId":"9070216","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Urea, (H<sub>2</sub>N)<sub>2</sub>CO, is excreted by mammals and can be used as a fertilizer.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The mass spectrum of urea is shown below.</p>\n<p><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4475/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-07_om_13.00.41.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/01.j_01\"></p>\n<p>Identify the species responsible for the peaks at <em>m</em>/<em>z </em>= 60 and 44.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/adfa1bd27f3c7d0d30adf9528155605a337d1857.png\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>60</em>: CON<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub><sup>+</sup></p>\n<p><em>44</em>: CONH<sub>2</sub><sup>+</sup></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept “molecular ion”.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong><br></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070216","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ1.1j","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The mass spectrum of urea is shown below. Identify the species responsible for the peaks at m/z = 60 and 44.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"j","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.3 Spectroscopic identification of organic compounds","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}